The paper deals with the deployment of mobile routers for maintaining connectivity among autonomous agents exploring an area. This involves network infrastructure, robotics, and distributed systems, which are all relevant to the sub-category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of simple robotic routers and the proposed algorithms for their deployment also fall under the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithms are localized and distributed, which suggests that they involve some form of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The agents are autonomous, which implies that there is some level of machine learning or artificial intelligence involved, making the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) relevant. Finally, the paper deals with the coordination and communication between agents, which is also relevant to the sub-category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
